Boil a full #kettle{}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, fry the @chicken thigh{240%g}(diced), ~{8-10%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, pour the boiled water into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} on high heat.

Boil the @spaghetti{180%g}, ~{8%minutes}.

Once the chicken is cooked, stir in the @tomato puree{30%g}, @creme fraiche{75%g}, @harissa paste{50%g}(add less if you'd prefer things milder), @red wine stock paste{28%g}, @sugar{1%tsp} and @water{125%ml}.

Bring to the boil then simmer, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add the @baby spinach{100%g} in handfuls, making sure it's piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir through the @hard Italian style cheese{20%g}(grated).

Once the pasta is cooked, drain and add to the sauce. Toss to coat.

Share the pasta between your bowls.

Enjoy!